(344, 1, '2015-06-30 08:21:59', '2015-06-30 08:21:59', 'Black Swan State Theatre Company has recently launched its 2015 season which contains a mix of classics, comedies, an exciting new Australian work, a musical and a family production. The year begins with Venus In Fur by David Ives as part of the FRINGE WORLD Festival, followed by Dinner by Moira Buffini, Glengarry Glen Ross by David Mamet and Noël Coward’s Blithe Spirit. The World Premiere of Extinction by Hannie Rayson follows with a first in family theatre for the company with Albert Lamorisse’s The Red Balloon, adapted by Hilary Bell and featured as part of the AWESOME Festival. The year concludes with the electrifying rock musical Next To Normal with book and lyrics by Brian Yorkey and music by Tom Kitt. Subscribers can choose between 3, 4 and 5 play and Opening Night 5 play and Closing Night 5 play subscription packages. Black Swan also offers an affordable 3 play preview/matinee package, enabling subscribers to see three previews and/or matinees of their choice for only $153. A 3 play student subscription package is also available for just $87. Subscribing comes with added benefits, like access to the best seats in the house, great prices, free ticket exchanges and exclusive discounts and experiences. And the opportunity for early subscribers to win one of 3 great prizes, including a return trip for two from Perth to Paris on Singapore Airlines!', 'Black Swan State Theatre Company 2015 Season', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'black-swan-state-theatre-company-2015-season', '', '', '2015-06-30 08:40:26', '2015-06-30 08:40:26', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=events&#038;p=344', 0, 'events', '', 0),
