(347, 1, '2015-07-01 00:00:10', '2015-07-01 00:00:10', 'For Love of Country will mark the Gallery’s contribution to Perth’s commemoration of the 100th Anniversary of the First World War and the Australian Gallipoli campaign. Drawn from the State Art Collection, this exhibition presents a compelling mix of historical works from the First and Second World Wars, together with contemporary works that reflect on wider issues and conflicts.', 'For Love of Country', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'for-love-of-country', '', '', '2015-07-01 00:02:32', '2015-07-01 00:02:32', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=events&#038;p=347', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(348, 1, '2015-07-01 00:06:11', '2015-07-01 00:06:11', 'Fasten your seatbelts, stow your tray table and ensure your seat is in the upright position, because the newest addition to the Scitech floor is about to touch down. The Going Places exhibition will land 9 May with bags full of science fun in tow! Going Places explores the technology we have developed to transport ourselves and goods around the world, and lets visitors pilot an airship, ride on a hovercraft or control traffic in a big city. “Whether we’re grabbing groceries that have come from another country, or whether we’re jumping in the car to go to work, transport touches us all every day,” Scitech CEO Alan Brien said. “This exhibition takes a closer look at the technology behind all kinds of transport and lets visitors discover the incredible inventions that make the farthest reaches of our planet accessible.”', 'Going Places Exhibition', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'going-places-exhibition', '', '', '2015-07-01 00:06:11', '2015-07-01 00:06:11', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=events&#038;p=348', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(349, 1, '2015-07-01 00:09:25', '2015-07-01 00:09:25', 'Experience the thrill of thoroughbred racing at Belmont Park Racecourse. Each day will feature an exciting eight race programme and access to trackside food &amp; beverage outlets, informal dining, betting facilities and amenities. Free Parking is available. Gates open at 9am so get your family and friends together and be part of the racing action. A day at Belmont Park has never been more economical with the introduction of the ‘Belmont Bonanza’, spend $20 and receive over $67 in value. Inclusions: General Admission, two drink vouchers, racebook, $5.00 Betting Voucher, Free General Admission Ticket for a non carnival day, free parking is available.', 'Saturday''s at Belmont Park Racecource', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'saturdays-at-belmont-park-racecource', '', '', '2015-07-01 00:09:25', '2015-07-01 00:09:25', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=events&#038;p=349', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(350, 1, '2015-07-01 00:12:23', '2015-07-01 00:12:23', 'Quiet moments showcases the work of some of the premier photographers from the UK, Europe and Australia. Poetic photography is distinctive for cutting juxtaposition and languid beauty, offering many possible meanings in stark contrast to the majority of advertising and online imagery saturating today''s media.Curated by Susan Hill, the works presented feature strange scenes, peculiar figures and random objects from everyday life combined in unexpected ways. Rich in colour, hidden meaning and metaphor, viewers are invited to contemplate the images and project their own day dreams into the scenes. Quiet moments features the work of eight prominent national and international photographers.', 'Quiet Moments: Contemporary Poetic Photography', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'quiet-moments-contemporary-poetic-photography', '', '', '2015-07-01 00:12:23', '2015-07-01 00:12:23', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=events&#038;p=350', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(351, 1, '2015-07-01 00:14:39', '2015-07-01 00:14:39', 'The 2015 WA Architecture Awards entries will be on display in the Brookfield Place Lobby. View some of the best in WA architecture across a range of categories including Public Architecture, Educational Architecture, Residential Architecture – Houses (New), Residential Architecture – Houses (Alterations &amp; Additions), Residential Architecture – Multiple Housing, Heritage, Urban Design, Commercial Architecture, Interior Architecture, Small Project Architecture and Sustainable Architecture. This year, three iconic Perth buildings are eligible for the Enduring Architecture category, which recognises buildings that remain important in a contemporary context. Whether you’re looking to build or renovate your home or are curious to know more about some of Perth’s newest buildings, this is a unique opportunity to see a wide range of recent projects. 8.30am – 5pm, Monday – Friday.', 'WA Architecture Awards ''Exhibitions of Entries''', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'wa-architecture-awards-exhibitions-of-entries', '', '', '2015-07-01 00:14:39', '2015-07-01 00:14:39', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=events&#038;p=351', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(352, 1, '2015-07-01 00:16:51', '2015-07-01 00:16:51', 'Winter Garden brings Western Australia an enchanting experience for the young and the young at heart. The idyllic surrounds of the Fremantle Esplanade Park will be transformed into a magical festival dedicated to the delights and traditional wonders of a white winter. Attractions include the return of Australia’s biggest outdoor ice rink, falling snow, a mountainous pop-up slide, carnival rides, plus music and entertainment for all ages! Winter Garden is free to enter, although tickets must be purchased for ice skating and some activities. Come and enjoy the pop-up lodge where there will be food and drinks that are fun for the little ones and grown-ups alike. Or, visit the themed photo booths to capture a raft of memories and moments to be shared.', 'Winter Garden', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'winter-garden', '', '', '2015-07-01 00:16:51', '2015-07-01 00:16:51', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=events&#038;p=352', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(353, 1, '2015-07-01 00:20:00', '2015-07-01 00:20:00', 'This winter holidays, bring the kids to enjoy the novelty of sliding down an icy slope in the heart of Perth city. Smaller kids can ride the 4m slide, while bigger kids (over 120cm tall) can enjoy a 12m slide. Free tickets must be secured online in advance. Choose from 12 sessions daily of 25 minutes each. Suitable for ages 3 -12 years', 'Perth City Snow Slide', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'perth-city-snow-slide', '', '', '2015-07-01 00:20:00', '2015-07-01 00:20:00', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=events&#038;p=353', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(354, 1, '2015-07-01 00:21:50', '2015-07-01 00:21:50', 'Since its inception six years ago, the PICA Salon Vernissage has developed a reputation for being one of the most sophisticated events on the Perth arts calendar - a stunning evening of art, fashion, music and performance, the PICA Salon Vernissage is an art-collectors dream. All the works on display are for sale, providing a platform for both seasoned and new art collectors to add to their collections, with all proceeds going directly to the artists. PICA Salon: Epic Narratives features the works of 19 local, national and international artists exploring the concept "Epic Narratives" through a variety of media including painting, drawing, sculpture, photography, installation, video and performance. All of the works can be viewed online. The exhibition runs for a period of 6 weeks from 5 July - 16 August and includes numerous special events as part of the public program.', 'PICA Salon: Epic Narratives', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'pica-salon-epic-narratives', '', '', '2015-07-01 00:21:50', '2015-07-01 00:21:50', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=events&#038;p=354', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(355, 1, '2015-07-01 00:24:54', '2015-07-01 00:24:54', 'Judith is back on stage with her first new solo show since 2012 and the good news is that her last year really sucked. A truly awful year for Judith always leads to a great show for her fans and 2014 was magnificently terrible. Think death and early menopause and you''ll be in the ballpark. Always hilarious, honest and occasionally shocking, Judith doesn''t write a show unless she has something to say and she''s more than ready for this one. It is virtually impossible to imagine the Australian comedy scene without Judith Lucy and luckily this year, you won''t have to. After three years off the stage she''s back in Perth for two nights only at the Perth Concert Hall', 'Judith Lucy - Ask No Questions of Moth', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'judith-lucy-ask-no-questions-of-moth', '', '', '2015-07-01 00:24:54', '2015-07-01 00:24:54', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=events&#038;p=355', 0, 'events', '', 0),
