(395, 1, '2015-07-01 08:47:14', '2015-07-01 08:47:14', 'Perth restaurants offer a distinctive array of fresh produce to satisfy all palates and budgets. Well known for its exceptional quality and out of the ordinary cuisine, Perth is a food lovers paradise.\r\n\r\nA vast selection of dining choices include fine dining at the five star hotels, a casual pub lunch at the water’s edge in East Perth, or wine and tapas at one of the many laneway bars. Since a change in licensing laws in 2007, over 50 small bars have emerged throughout the city, all offering different cuisine and character. The ''West End'' in the city offers a good selection of quality restaurants and bars, which is only a five minute walk west from the CBD. Every Friday night from October to March, Forrest Chase transforms into a food lovers paradise with the Twilight Hawkers Market. Enjoy delicious dishes from all corners of the world, tastes from a melting pot of international cultures such as Indonesian Satays, Malaysian curries, Turkish gozlemes, Moroccan tagines, Colombian Empanadas, Mexican Burritos and Japanese. Cross cultural influences continue with the entertainment – live music from local artists and bands from all over Perth.\r\n\r\nOur wineries are recognised as some of the best in the world where you can chose from over 100 wineries and restaurants in the famous Swan Valley to sample world class wines and fresh produce such as chocolate, coffee and cheese. See the Swan Valley section under East of Perth for more information.\r\n\r\nA popular dining area is Northbridge, just across the railway line in the city and walking distance from the CBD. Northbridge is a vibrant area with cafés, restaurants, bars, shops, nightlife, plenty of alfresco street dining with an Italian and Asian influence. Mt Lawley, only five minutes further north by car, offers the Beaufort Street strip with a selection of quality restaurants, pubs, shops and a buzzing atmosphere day or night.\r\n\r\nFremantle is famous for its fishing heritage and you can’t visit WA without tasting the fresh, succulent fish and chips by the ocean’s edge at the Fishing Boat Harbour. Enjoy the Italian influence of pizza and pasta restaurants along the ‘Cappuccino Strip’ with plenty of alfesco dining to enjoy the balmy evenings, or visit one of the stylish microbreweries. Little Creatures in the Fishing Boat Harbour is very popular. The Fremantle Markets is full of fresh, gourmet food stalls with a huge selection of local produce such as fruit and vegetables, bread, honey, coffee and cheese. Following is a selection of restaurants and pub choices.', 'Wine & Dine', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'wine-dine', '', '', '2015-07-01 08:47:14', '2015-07-01 08:47:14', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?page_id=395', 0, 'page', '', 0),
