(452, 1, '2015-07-08 04:42:52', '2015-07-08 04:42:52', 'The Duyfken, a replica of the 1606 Dutch ship, was created to tell the story of the early European exploration of the Australian coastline. Captain Janszoon was the first European to map and record Australia in history so Duyfken''s voyage marks the beginning of Australia''s recorded history. The Duyfken is a floating museum and offers a guided tour where you can step back in history four centuries. The ship has now moved to the Mounts Bay Sailing Club, Australia II drive, Crawley. Open 10am - 4pm weekdays and 10am - 5pm weekends.', 'The Duyfken', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-duyfken', '', '', '2015-07-08 04:42:52', '2015-07-08 04:42:52', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=452', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
