(468, 1, '2015-07-08 05:03:43', '2015-07-08 05:03:43', 'In 1606, the small Dutch ship Duyfken sailed from the Indonesian island of Banda in search of gold and trade opportunities on the fabled island of Nova Guinea. They sailed beyond Papua New Guinea and explored and chartered part of the coast of Nova Guinea. They did not find gold - but they did find the northern coast of a huge continent: Australia. Captain Janszoon was the first European to map and record Australia in history so Duyfken''s voyage marks the beginning of Australia''s recorded history. The Duyfken Replica is now open to the public. Open 10am to 4pm weekdays and 10am to 5pm weekends. ', 'Duyfken 1606 Replica', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'duyfken-1606-replica', '', '', '2015-07-08 05:03:43', '2015-07-08 05:03:43', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=468', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(469, 1, '2015-07-08 05:07:07', '2015-07-08 05:07:07', 'The Western Australian Visitor Centre at its new premises in 55 William Street can assist with everything to help you enjoy your holiday. The friendly staff can book accommodation or tours, answer any questions and also have a wide selection of brochures on places of interest throughout Perth and Western Australia. They are located just west of the Murray Street Mall, in the CBD. ', 'WA Visitor Centre', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'wa-visitor-centre', '', '', '2015-07-08 05:07:07', '2015-07-08 05:07:07', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=469', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
