(483, 1, '2015-07-08 06:00:17', '2015-07-08 06:00:17', 'Located at Barrack Square, overlooking the picturesque Swan River is one of Perth’s most unique tourist attractions. Filled with fascinating historic content, the Bell Tower includes the twelve bells of St Martin-in-the-Fields, which are recorded as being in existence from before the 14th century and recast in the 16th century by Queen Elizabeth I. From one of London’s most famous churches, the St Martin-in-the-Fields bells have rung out to celebrate many historic events such as England’s victory over the Spanish Armada in 1588 and the WW11 victory at El Alamein in 1942. ', 'The Bell Tower', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-bell-tower', '', '', '2015-07-15 06:24:22', '2015-07-15 06:24:22', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=483', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
