(499, 1, '2015-07-08 06:39:37', '2015-07-08 06:39:37', 'The Western Australia Cricket Association is the home of cricket in WA and through the museum displays the history of cricket and other sports played at this famous ground. Visitors can do a tour of the ground and see where the legends of cricket are made while gaining an understanding of the significance of the WACA to Western Australia’s sporting history. The museum is open Monday to Friday from 10am to 3pm, and Grounds Tours operate Monday to Friday 10am and 1pm. There are no tours on match days, weekends or public holidays. Catch the free Red or Yellow CAT bus from Perth to the WACA.', 'WACA Ground Tours & Museum', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'waca-ground-tours-museum', '', '', '2015-07-08 06:39:37', '2015-07-08 06:39:37', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=499', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
