(512, 1, '2015-07-08 07:29:30', '2015-07-08 07:29:30', 'King Street has a very European feel with its early 20th century, low rise architecture and restored facades. Commonly known locally as the ‘West End’, King Street specialises mainly in designer stores and trendy cafes and bars making it one of the most exclusive addresses in the city. There are over a dozen stores including Louis Vuitton, Kookai, Gucci, Prada, Bally, Chanel, Sass & Bide, Empire Rose, Tiffany & Co, Georg Jensen and TAG Heuer. King Street was named in honour of King William 1V in 1845 and is heritage listed. It''s only a five minute walk west from the CBD.', 'King Street', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'king-street', '', '', '2015-07-08 07:29:30', '2015-07-08 07:29:30', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=512', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
