(514, 1, '2015-07-08 07:33:01', '2015-07-08 07:33:01', 'Only a ten minute walk east of Perth you will find Claisebrook Cove, a picturesque and vibrant inlet offering residents and visitors a selection of river side cafes, restaurants and the Royal on the Waterfront Pub. Ideal for walking, picnicking, rollerblading, cycling, fishing, kayaking and of course dining. Dine alfresco while enjoying the views and watching the boats come and go. Within the area you can visit the Charnock Woman, a 25 metre pavement mosiac in Victoria Gardens, East Perth. This 25 metre mosaic tells the Bibbullmun Dreamtime story of the evil Charnock Woman who used her hair to trap children.', 'Claisebrook Cove East Perth', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'claisebrook-cove-east-perth', '', '', '2015-07-08 07:33:01', '2015-07-08 07:33:01', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=514', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
