(520, 1, '2015-07-08 07:37:30', '2015-07-08 07:37:30', 'Take a stroll back in time when visiting Perth''s iconic London Court, just off the Hay Street Mall in the city. Built in 1937 as a combination of residential and commercial premises for a wealthy gold miner, London Court captures a setting and atmosphere of Tudor England which is an architectural delight. At the decorative Hay Street Mall entrance, a blue faced clock chimes every quarter of an hour. The clock face is a replica of the ''Great Clock'' at Rouen in France. London Court is a shopper''s delight offering Aboriginal art, hand made jewellery, souvenirs, opals, diamonds, gourmet chocolate and much more.', 'London Court', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'london-court', '', '', '2015-07-08 07:37:40', '2015-07-08 07:37:40', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=520', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
