(524, 1, '2015-07-08 07:44:15', '2015-07-08 07:44:15', 'Subiaco, often referred to as Subi by Perth locals, is one of Perth''s urban villages and is situated five kilometres west from the CBD, accessible from Perth and Fremantle by train on the Fremantle line. Subiaco offers premier shopping, markets, restaurants, cafes, bars and clubs, and has several art galleries, museums, theatres, parks and gardens which makes it a popular tourist destination. Subiaco is well known for its numerous shops specialising in Australian pearls, and the popular Station Street Markets which is opposite the train station, open Friday to Sunday.', 'Subiaco', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'subiaco', '', '', '2015-07-08 07:44:15', '2015-07-08 07:44:15', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=524', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
