(537, 1, '2015-07-08 08:51:32', '2015-07-08 08:51:32', 'Kings Park and Botanical Gardens are visited by over six million people a year, with good reason. With its remarkable expanses of unique bushland and tranquil parkland the park is the most popular destination in WA. It is said to be the largest city park in the world at 400.6 hectares. It was first opened for public use in 1872. The total area of the park overlooks the Swan River and Darling Range and showcases an outstanding collection of WA flora, is a popular place for picnics and walks and has sweeping views of the city and Swan River. You''ll also find a cafe, restaurant, Aboriginal art gallery and shop.', 'Kings Park', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kings-park', '', '', '2015-07-08 08:51:32', '2015-07-08 08:51:32', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=537', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
