(579, 1, '2015-07-09 02:28:09', '2015-07-09 02:28:09', 'The Fremantle Arts Centre is a multi-arts organisation which was built by convicts in 1864. This historic site was originally the first purpose built ‘lunatic asylum’ in WA, and in 1909 it was declared a Poor House, which housed poor and elderley women. It has a lovely courtyard cafe and retail gallery, showcasing the finest handmade gifts, jewellery and art. It''s one of Australia’s leadings arts organisations with a diverse year-round cultural program. FAC has dynamic exhibitions, the finest WA-made wares for sale, an expansive live music program and special events. Open 7 days. ', 'Fremantle Arts Centre', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'fremantle-arts-centre', '', '', '2015-07-09 02:28:09', '2015-07-09 02:28:09', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=579', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
