(581, 1, '2015-07-09 02:32:14', '2015-07-09 02:32:14', 'The Army Museum of WA displays the history of WA men and women who served in the Army in conflicts from the Boer War to Afganistan. Displays include memorabilia, medals, photos, vehicle and artillery pieces. The museum is located in the Artillery Barracks site in Burt Street Fremantle. This entire precinct has been heritage listed with several of the buildings having historical significance. Each gallery reflects the Army in Western Australia and Western Australian’s service within the army from the colonial period through to the present day.', 'The Army Museum of WA', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-army-museum-of-wa', '', '', '2015-07-09 02:32:14', '2015-07-09 02:32:14', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=581', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
