(587, 1, '2015-07-09 03:38:31', '2015-07-09 03:38:31', 'The Shipwreck Galleries is recognised as the foremost maritime archaeology museum in the southern hemisphere. The Museum is housed in 1850s-era Commissariat building and has since been restored to its historic glory. Steeped in history, the galleries house hundreds of relics from ships wrecked along WA’s treacherous coastline, including the original timbers from the Batavia (wrecked in 1629), the de Vlamingh plate, and also countless artefacts from the Dutch shipwrecks Zuytdorp, Zeewijk and Vergulde Draeck. Open daily 9.30am - 5pm. Free entry. Suggested donation $5.', 'The Shipwreck Galleries', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-shipwreck-galleries', '', '', '2015-07-09 07:12:48', '2015-07-09 07:12:48', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=587', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(588, 1, '2015-07-09 03:40:51', '2015-07-09 03:40:51', 'Located in a magnificent historical warehouse building on Victoria Quay, in the centre of the Fremantle Port, E Shed Markets is two minues from the Railway Station and right next door to the Fremantle Maritime Museum and the Rottnest Ferry Terminals. With a massive licensed alfresco terrace looking over Fremantle''s picturesque working harbour, E-Shed Markets is the only waterfront market in Western Australia. Watch the boats and ships passing by, enjoy international food and music, and shop for local handicrafts, antiques and collectables, fashion both vintage and new and fresh organic fruit and vegetables.', 'E Shed Markets', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'e-shed-markets', '', '', '2015-07-09 07:13:05', '2015-07-09 07:13:05', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=588', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
