(634, 1, '2015-07-10 01:07:33', '2015-07-10 01:07:33', 'It’s well worth visiting the remarkable Stromatolites at the picturesque Lake Thetis near Cervantes if you are in the area. Enjoy a walk around the lake and witness the earth’s oldest living life form, believed to be over 2,000 years old. Stromatolites are among the world’s oldest fossils, some of which are over 3.5 billion years old, and provide some of the most ancient records of life on Earth. They may look like rocks but they are in fact living things! You will find the best examples of Stromatolites at the south western edge of the lake, with a beach and bush walk trail available.', 'Stromatolites', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'stromatolites', '', '', '2015-07-10 01:07:33', '2015-07-10 01:07:33', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=634', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(635, 1, '2015-07-10 01:07:17', '2015-07-10 01:07:17', '', 'stromatolites', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'stromatolites', '', '', '2015-07-10 01:07:17', '2015-07-10 01:07:17', '', 634, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/stromatolites.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(636, 1, '2015-07-10 01:11:07', '2015-07-10 01:11:07', 'Jurien Bay is a relaxed fishing town a three hour drive north of Perth. It''s blessed with long sandy beaches, colourful offshore reefs, amazing marine life and a thriving cray fishing industry. Protected by the Jurien Bay Marine Park, these habitats are also a haven for the rare Australian sea lion and you can join a fishing charter for close encounters with sea lions, dolphins, and during the migration season from June to December, the majestic hump back whales. Visit the Pinnacles Visitor Centre in Cadiz Street, Cervantes on the way for more information.', 'Jurien Bay', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'jurien-bay', '', '', '2015-07-10 01:11:07', '2015-07-10 01:11:07', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=636', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
