(677, 1, '2015-07-10 02:47:06', '2015-07-10 02:47:06', 'John Forrest National Park is 24 kilometres east of Perth and is Western Australia''s oldest park, with numerous walk trails, BBQ facilities and magnificent views. As early as 1898, the land was reserved for conservation and recreation. Two years later, it was named Greenmount National Park and in 1947 the name was changed to commemorate Sir John Forrest, who was the Premier of Western Australia between 1890 and 1901. Several trails run through various parts of the park, including the Railway Heritage Trail, which follows the alignment of the old railway line to York. ', 'John Forrest National Park', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'john-forrest-national-park', '', '', '2015-07-10 02:47:06', '2015-07-10 02:47:06', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=677', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(678, 1, '2015-07-10 02:46:53', '2015-07-10 02:46:53', '', 'John-Forrest-National-Park', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'john-forrest-national-park', '', '', '2015-07-10 02:46:53', '2015-07-10 02:46:53', '', 677, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/John-Forrest-National-Park.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(679, 1, '2015-07-10 02:48:41', '2015-07-10 02:48:41', '30 minutes east of Perth lies the quaint town of Kalamunda, which offers fantastic views of the city and coastal plains, plenty of bush walking, wineries, orchards, art galleries and a peaceful rural atmosphere. The region has five national parks, over 30 well marked walk trails including the beginning of the famous Bibbulmun track which stretches nearly 1000 kilometres from Kalamunda to Albany on the south coast. On the first Saturday of every month browse the stalls of quality craft, arts and locally made produce at the Kalamunda Village Markets. Contact the Kalamunda Visitor Centre for more information.', 'Kalamunda', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kalamunda', '', '', '2015-07-10 02:48:41', '2015-07-10 02:48:41', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=679', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(680, 1, '2015-07-10 02:48:32', '2015-07-10 02:48:32', '', 'Kalamunda', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'kalamunda', '', '', '2015-07-10 02:48:32', '2015-07-10 02:48:32', '', 679, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Kalamunda.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(681, 1, '2015-07-10 02:53:52', '2015-07-10 02:53:52', 'The Shire of Mundaring covers an area of 644 square kilometres and one third of its total area is State Forest. The area is rich in history, closely linked by the old railway line that is now the fabulous Railway Reserves Heritage Trail stretching 59kms through the shire. The amazing engineering feat that is the Mundaring Weir with the water pipeline to the Eastern Goldfields region is also here, and the Mundaring Weir Hotel, which is over 100 years old and serves great pub food, is worth visiting. There are also galleries, restaurants, parks and trails. Drop into the Visitor Centre for more information.', 'Mundaring', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'mundaring', '', '', '2015-07-10 02:54:28', '2015-07-10 02:54:28', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=681', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(682, 1, '2015-07-10 02:53:29', '2015-07-10 02:53:29', '', 'Mundaring', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'mundaring', '', '', '2015-07-10 02:53:29', '2015-07-10 02:53:29', '', 681, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Mundaring.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(683, 1, '2015-07-10 02:56:54', '2015-07-10 02:56:54', 'Enjoy a short ride or extended trek by camel and experience a whole new perspective of our Darling Scarp environment. The forest echoes to the calls of many native birds and it is possible to encounter kangaroos and wallabies, while the camels carry you quietly through the forest. In season magnificent displays of wildflowers are abundant. Have a picnic or relax in our pleasant tea rooms and you may meet the Camel Whisperer! Bookings are essential for our 1hr, half day and full day treks. Open seven days.', 'Calamunnda Camel Farm', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'calamunnda-camel-farm', '', '', '2015-07-10 02:56:54', '2015-07-10 02:56:54', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=683', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(684, 1, '2015-07-10 02:56:35', '2015-07-10 02:56:35', '', 'calamunndacamel', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'calamunndacamel', '', '', '2015-07-10 02:56:35', '2015-07-10 02:56:35', '', 683, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/calamunndacamel.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(685, 1, '2015-07-10 02:59:30', '2015-07-10 02:59:30', 'Araluen Botanic Park is Heaven in the Hills – an extraordinary garden in a breathtakingly beautiful setting, located in the Darling Range, just 35km south-east of the Perth CBD. Open from daily from 9am – 6pm (except Christmas Day), the unique hills setting and north-south valley aspect make Araluen a very special and world-class garden, like nothing else in Western Australia. Enjoy lunch or a devonshire tea in the Chalet Healy Restaurant, walk the trails, picnic and purchase gifts from the gift store.', 'Araluen Botanical Park', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'araluen-botanical-park', '', '', '2015-07-10 02:59:30', '2015-07-10 02:59:30', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=685', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(686, 1, '2015-07-10 02:59:17', '2015-07-10 02:59:17', '', 'Araluen', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'araluen', '', '', '2015-07-10 02:59:17', '2015-07-10 02:59:17', '', 685, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Araluen.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(687, 1, '2015-07-10 03:00:50', '2015-07-10 03:00:50', 'Only thirty minutes drive from Perth City and located behind the town of Kalamunda, the Bickley Valley comprises of ten boutique wineries, and a bio-dynamic cider house that can all be discovered along this drive trail. Vistas of vineyards and orchards in the valley and the regions hilly terrain, make motoring a delight and driving into the Perth Hills to sample the vintner’s wares is a very pleasant day trip. Cellar doors are all open at the weekend and most will open during the week by appointment only. Visitors are encouraged to phone ahead to check opening times.', 'Bickley Valley Wine Trail', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'bickley-valley-wine-trail', '', '', '2015-07-10 03:00:50', '2015-07-10 03:00:50', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=687', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(688, 1, '2015-07-10 03:00:38', '2015-07-10 03:00:38', '', 'Bickley-Valley-Wine-Trail', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'bickley-valley-wine-trail', '', '', '2015-07-10 03:00:38', '2015-07-10 03:00:38', '', 687, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Bickley-Valley-Wine-Trail.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(689, 1, '2015-07-10 03:02:29', '2015-07-10 03:02:29', 'The Bibbulmun Track is one of the world’s great long distance walk trails, stretching nearly 1000km from Kalamunda in the Perth Hills, to Albany on the south coast, winding through the heart of the scenic South West of Western Australia. The Bibbulmun Track offers a wide range of experiences, from a gentle stroll to enjoy the peace and beauty of the natural environment, to an epic eight week adventure. The Track is for walkers only and is signposted with yellow triangular markers, and starts in Kalamunda which is only 30 minutes east of Perth, in the Perth Hills. ', 'Bibbulmun Track', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'bibbulmun-track', '', '', '2015-07-10 03:02:29', '2015-07-10 03:02:29', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=689', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(690, 1, '2015-07-10 03:02:18', '2015-07-10 03:02:18', '', 'Bibbulmen-Track', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'bibbulmen-track', '', '', '2015-07-10 03:02:18', '2015-07-10 03:02:18', '', 689, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Bibbulmen-Track.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(691, 1, '2015-07-10 03:03:46', '2015-07-10 03:03:46', 'Charming country towns, rolling hills, historic buildings telling stories of our pioneer past, winding streams and stunning views sum up the Avon Valley. East of Perth, the Avon Valley region incorporates the towns of Beverley, Chittering, Goomalling, New Norcia, Northam, Toodyay, Victoria Plains and York, all within an easy two hour drive of Perth. Explore the area and stay at one of the many quaint accommodation choices; historic hotels, country inns, cosy bed & breakfasts or shady caravan parks. Enjoy locally produced food and wine and learn about the first inland settlement of Western Australia. ', 'Avon Valley', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'avon-valley', '', '', '2015-07-10 03:03:46', '2015-07-10 03:03:46', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=691', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(692, 1, '2015-07-10 03:03:34', '2015-07-10 03:03:34', '', 'Avon-Valley', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'avon-valley', '', '', '2015-07-10 03:03:34', '2015-07-10 03:03:34', '', 691, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Avon-Valley.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(693, 1, '2015-07-10 03:07:06', '2015-07-10 03:07:06', 'In 1848, two Spanish Benedictine monks traveled to WA and set up a mission which they developed into the New Norcia Mission and Farm. Named after Norcia in Italy, the Benedictine community of Roman Catholic monks befriended and worked closely with the local Aboriginal people teaching them farming skills and supplying them with food. New Norcia is the only Monastic town in Australia, where monks live, work and pray. Visit the fascinating Museum and Art Gallery, enjoy a pub lunch at the 1927 New Norcia Hotel, stay at the peaceful Monastery and listen to the monks Gregorian chants at certain times during the day.', 'New Norcia', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'new-norcia', '', '', '2015-07-10 03:07:06', '2015-07-10 03:07:06', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=693', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(694, 1, '2015-07-10 03:06:53', '2015-07-10 03:06:53', '', 'New-Norcia', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-norcia', '', '', '2015-07-10 03:06:53', '2015-07-10 03:06:53', '', 693, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/New-Norcia.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(695, 1, '2015-07-10 03:08:28', '2015-07-10 03:08:28', 'An hour east of Perth, York is WA’s most historic inland town. First settled in 1831, it is now a popular tourist destination and reminder of life in the pioneering days. Governor James Stirling commissioned Ensign Robert Dale to explore east of the Darling Range, and in August 1830, Dale discovered what was to become the Avon Valley. The fertile countryside reminded them of England, and they named the locality York. Convicts were introduced to York in 1851 and did much to develop the district. York is best to visit Thursday to Sunday when everything is open!', 'York', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'york', '', '', '2015-07-10 03:08:28', '2015-07-10 03:08:28', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=695', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(696, 1, '2015-07-10 03:08:17', '2015-07-10 03:08:17', '', 'York', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'york', '', '', '2015-07-10 03:08:17', '2015-07-10 03:08:17', '', 695, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/York.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(697, 1, '2015-07-10 04:21:38', '2015-07-10 04:21:38', 'Adventure World is Perth’s premier theme park, home to 24 uniquely themed attractions including ‘Australia’s best Roller Coaster’ – the jaw-dropping $12m world class coaster ‘Abyss’, adrenaline pumping thrill rides, water rides, water slides, and an Australian wildlife experience where you have the opportunity to cuddle koalas! The Medieval themed ‘Dragon’s Kingdom’ is an enchanting land of cutesy dragons, enormous flowers & fairies with rides, slides & an aqua splash zone dedicated to the youngest adventures. Just 18 minutes from Perth and only 15 minutes from Fremantle.', 'Adventure World', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'adventure-world', '', '', '2015-07-10 04:21:38', '2015-07-10 04:21:38', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=697', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
