(699, 1, '2015-07-10 04:23:32', '2015-07-10 04:23:32', 'Perth is famous for its beaches and you will soon understand why. Locals and visitors alike flock to the coast to enjoy the sunshine, clean white sand and crystal clear blue waters, to swim, sunbathe, snorkel and relax. Smooth terraced lawns and towering Norfolk Pines makes Cottesloe Beach one of the most popular, only 20 minutes west of Perth on the way to Fremantle. City Beach, Scarborough, Trigg, Leighton, Swanbourne and Rockingham are all family friendly and easily accessible, all with a cafe nearby. Visit the WA Visitor Centre, 55 William Street, Perth for more information.', 'Beaches', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'beaches', '', '', '2015-07-10 04:23:32', '2015-07-10 04:23:32', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=699', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
(700, 1, '2015-07-10 04:23:14', '2015-07-10 04:23:14', '', 'Beaches', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'beaches', '', '', '2015-07-10 04:23:14', '2015-07-10 04:23:14', '', 699, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Beaches.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(701, 1, '2015-07-10 04:31:15', '2015-07-10 04:31:15', 'Rottnest Island is located 18 kilometres off the WA coast near Fremantle. It was inhabited by Aboriginal people until rising sea levels separated the island from the mainland of WA about 7,000 years ago. A popular holiday destination for locals and visitors, it’s a relaxed, car free island offering world class beaches and stunning bays, swimming, snorkelling and bike riding. Ferries will take you from Fremantle, Perth and Hillarys Boat Harbour, either for the day or there’s plenty of accommodation to chose from.', 'Rottnest Island', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rottnest-island', '', '', '2015-07-10 04:31:15', '2015-07-10 04:31:15', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=701', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
