(711, 1, '2015-07-10 05:31:14', '2015-07-10 05:31:14', 'Penguin Island lies in the clear waters of the Shoalwater Marine Park, only 45 minutes south of Perth where you can have the opportunity of getting up close with the smallest species of penguin in the world, the Little Penguin. Penguin Island has the largest known breeding colony in WA, and these very shy little birds are rarely seen in the wild but you can watch feedings and learn all about them at the Penguin Experience Discovery Centre with Rockingham Wild Encounters. Feeding times 10.30am, 12.30pm and 2.30pm.', 'Penguin Island', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'penguin-island', '', '', '2015-07-22 04:11:36', '2015-07-22 04:11:36', '', 0, 'http://111.93.163.213/Helloperth/php/?post_type=directories&#038;p=711', 0, 'directories', '', 0),
